        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 6:03PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 603 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pennville, or 7 miles northwest of Portland, moving northeast at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Portland, Berne, Geneva, Pennville, Westchester, Center, Bryant, and
Ceylon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
